# Pineapple Margarita

![](2F125077-66B7-4117-BFD7-56B9CD0EA02C.jpg)

## Ingredients

- Ice | 2 cups or as needed | 
- Pineapple Juice | 3 fluid ounces | 
- Tequila | 2 fluid ounces silver | 
- Sec | ¾ fluid ounce triple | 
- Lime Juice | ¾ fluid ounce freshly squeezed | 
- Salt | 1 tablespoon coarse or as needed | 
- Lime | 2 wedges | 

> pineapple wedge for garnish (optional)

## Directions

Fill a cocktail shaker half-full with ice. Add pineapple juice, tequila, triple sec, and lime juice to the shaker. Seal and shake vigorously until outside is frosted, 10 to 15 seconds.

Sprinkle salt onto a plate. Moisten the rim of a glass with a lime wedge. Press the moistened rim into the salt. Fill glass with ice.

Strain margarita into the glass and garnish with pineapple and lime wedge, if desired.

> Cook’s Note

> You can use Tajin instead of coarse salt to rim the glass.

